parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can cause the seat belt to become inoperable, leading to a lack of restraint in the event of an accident, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle breaks
the seat belt buckle does not latch
the seat belt buckle comes loose when locked
the seat belt buckle is hard to latch or unlatch
the seat belt buckle fails to retract
the seat belt buckle is inoperative.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lockup of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to become stuck, making it difficult or impossible to use, which can lead to a lack of restraint in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt retractor locks up
the seat belt is hard to retract
the seat belt does not retract.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt guide can cause the seat belt to become difficult to latch or unlatch, leading to a lack of restraint in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The plastic guide in the seat belt latch breaks
making it hard to latch the seat belt.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design of the crankshaft with too little metal left after the front journal can lead to premature failure due to metal fatigue, resulting in engine failure, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Crankshaft breakage
engine failure
accessory belt tension issues
premature wear on the crankshaft.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission fluid leaks can cause fires, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Transmission fluid leak
fire
engine failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wheel bearing/hub assembly can cause the wheel to vibrate or jerk violently, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially causing the wheel to fall off while driving.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences vibrations or jerking motions
especially at high speeds (around 50-60 mph)
the steering wheel vibrates or is off-center
the wheel feels loose or wobbly.
